{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":32400,"record_hash":"sha256:9aa1b92c5f17053d085dc1dd656f32ddb05e4625b582ecaa686fba18b62c976b","timestamp":"2026-05-11T18:02:08.862Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"previous_status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\nFix now: `MetadataScope` exposes ref topology as public API. `local_ref`, `remote_ref`, and `tracking_ref` bake the GitMeta sync layout into the scope primitive, and `remote_ref` appears unused outside the type itself. Since `MetadataScope` is re-exported publicly, this is a hard-to-change API commitment and leaks higher-level exchange/sync mechanics into a key-selection type. Prefer keeping ref construction `pub(crate)` or moving it behind `Session` plumbing. See [types.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/types.rs:270), [types.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/types.rs:323), [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/lib.rs:141).\\n\\nFix now: scope-name validation claims “ref-safe” but does not fully match Git ref rules. Names like `review.` and `foo@{bar` pass the current checks but can produce invalid refs later via `refs/{namespace}/local/{name}`. Use an existing Git ref validator if available, or at least cover trailing `.`, `@{`, and tests for invalid examples. See [types.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/types.rs:283) and [types.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/types.rs:378).\\n\\nFix now: public method docs underspecify important side effects and bypasses. `serialize_scope` scans hydrated SQLite rows and writes only the scoped local ref, but does not update the default materialization marker, does not apply filter routing, pruning, or `meta:local:` exclusion. `materialize_scope` reads `refs/{ns}/remotes/{scope}`, writes SQLite plus the scoped local ref, and also does not update the marker. Those are reasonable low-level primitives, but public docs should say so explicitly. See [session.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/session.rs:261), [session.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/session.rs:285), [serialize.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/serialize.rs:548), [materialize.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/materialize.rs:189).\\n\\nLeave alone: the core `MetadataKeyMatch::{Exact, Prefix}` shape is generic enough; the agentlog naming is confined to tests. `Prefix` being raw string-prefix matching is acceptable as long as callers choose delimiter-aware prefixes like `foo:`. See [types.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/types.rs:342).\\n\\nLeave alone: `Session::{serialize_scope, materialize_scope}` as operations seem like valid GitMeta plumbing primitives, not agentlog-specific APIs. The main issue is making their boundary contract explicit and trimming/refining public ref helpers, not renaming them to agentlog concepts.\"}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T18:02:08.862Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}